adjective.description: Consisting of eight parts or things.

verb.description: Make or become eight times as numerous or as large.
examples: the new town populations have trebled the additions to the rural community, and in the case of Massachusetts have octupled them
prices doubled and quadruple and octupled

origin: Early 17th century: from French octuple or Latin octuplus (both adjectives), from octo eight + -plus (as in duplus double).
